<TITLE>HOLLINGER &lt;HLG.TO> BUYS CANADIAN MAGAZINE</TITLE>
<DATELINE>    Toronto, June 18 - </DATELINE><BODY>Hollinger Inc said it purchased Saturday
Night, a Canadian general-interest magazine.
    Financial terms were not disclosed, but Hollinger said it
has no immediate plans for changes in senior editorial
personnel.
    Saturday Night, which publishes features and analyses of
current events, is celebrating its 100th anniversary and has a
circulation of about 120,000, according to a magazine
spokesman.
    Hollinger, which owns 58 pct of &lt;Daily Telegraph PLC>, also
today completed the acquisition of Unimedia Inc, a Quebec-based
publisher.
 Reuter
